<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-35-0727 </DOCNO><TEXT>A computer-based measuring strategy to determine spatial orientation ofshort glass fibers from the cross-section of single fibers is presented.A way of correcting the inclination-dependent probability of hittinga fiber is shown as well as the correction of fiber-end intersections.The latter is done by pattern recognition and application of a set ofFORTRAN subroutines. 9 references.</TEXT></DOC>